---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="How I Listen: A Practical Podcast Philosophy | Jevan Goldsmith"
  description="Notes on listening for judgment, taste, decision-making, and a better personal operating system."
  canonical="https://jevangoldsmith.com/podcast-philosophy.html"
  bodyClass="nav-compact"
>
  <style slot="head" is:inline set:html={`
    .page-header .container,
    main.container {
      max-width: none;
      padding: 0 1rem;
    }
    .reading-philosophy-content {
      max-width: none;
      padding-left: 0;
      padding-right: 0;
    }
    @media (min-width: 769px) {
      .page-header .container,
      main.container {
        padding: 0 3rem;
      }
    }
  `} />
  <header class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>How I Listen</h1>
      <p>A practical podcast philosophy for taste, leverage, and ideas worth carrying.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="container">
    <article class="reading-philosophy-content">
      <section class="philosophy-section">
        <h2>Why I Listen</h2>
        <p>Podcasts give me access to long-form thinking from operators, investors, builders, and writers I would otherwise never meet. The good ones compress decades of judgment into a few hours of conversation.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="philosophy-section">
        <h2>How I Choose Shows</h2>
        <p>I follow people, not shows. If a host asks better questions than the room, I keep coming back. I drop shows that drift into news, ad reads, and recycled takes.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="philosophy-section">
        <h2>How I Listen</h2>
        <p>I listen at 1.3x on walks, at the gym, and on long drives. When something lands I stop, replay it, and write down the sentence in plain English. The note is the asset, not the listen.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="philosophy-section">
        <h2>What I Look For</h2>
        <p>Specifics over abstractions. Lived experience over commentary. Distinctions that change how I would act next time. The best episodes survive a re-listen six months later.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="philosophy-section">
        <h2>Where to Go Next</h2>
        <p>Start with the curated picks on the podcasts page. The "Must Listen" badge marks the episodes I keep returning to.</p>
      </section>

      <div class="back-to-books">
        <a href="/podcasts.html" class="back-link">&larr; Back to Podcasts</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Base>
